<TITLE> BDR deployed ahead of CCC polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) soldiers have been deployed at Chittagong metropolitan city on Wednesday ahead of the upcoming city corporation polls. The Chittagong City Corporation elections are scheduled on June 17. A statement signed by BDR public relations officer Muhammad Mohsin Reza announced the deployment. The statement said that BDR was deployed to assist non-military administration to maintain law and order in the election area. Mohsin Reza told bdnews24.com, "232 armed BDR members of different ranks, including officers will be on duty until the polls end." b
